pkg-explorer (0.2.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Started adding documentation.
  * Enhanced the packaging of pkg-explorer.
  * Ensured that the name is "pkg-explorer" everywhere.
  * Updated different dialogs with the new/removed features.
  * Always turn on the --force-file-info on installation.
  * Updated progress dialogs with the new wpkg_output.
  * Allows a Cancel button in progress dialogs.
  * Added a License dialog.
  * Fixes to the remove/purge functionality.
  * Added command line --help and --version options.

 -- Doug Barbieri <doug@m2osw.com>  Mon, 02 Sep 2013 13:53:51 -0800

pkg-explorer (0.2.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * When adding a software package source from the filesystem, "file:", the
    two path suffixes are converted into dist and component, respectively.
  * Took out build menu/toolbar entry since this is not supported (yet).
  * Fixed Import feature; validation was "missing".
  * Fixed the Purge; deconfigure() must be called explicitly.
  * Fixed package and environment in general.
  * Renamed the project with the "r" (exploreR).

 -- Doug Barbieri <doug@m2osw.com>  Thu, 18 Apr 1013 13:53:51 -0800

pkg-explorer (0.2.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Can now upgrade from the package repository via the InstallDialog class.
  * Got rid of Qt4 warnings via pragmas for GCC. Now builds with -WError under linux.
  * Fixed backwards log problem in the LogView. Now uses a fifo instead of a stack.
  * Added display of X-PrimarySection and X-SecondarySection in the WebView.
  * Debian package now has the correct icon and .desktop file so it will appear in the menu.
  * Install now only installs those checked packages instead of them all.
  * Uses new functionality available in libdebpackages where dependencies come from the index. Must faster now.
  * Added messagebox to show what will be installed and updated, including new packages.

 -- Doug Barbieri <doug@m2osw.com>  Thu, 08 Apr 2013 13:53:51 -0800

pkg-explorer (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added support for package source management (Debian-standard software source urls)
  * Now installs, imports and removes packages, plus updates sources.
  * Improved ProcessDialog so you can cancel the operation, and added a progress bar.
  * Now works with 0.8.0 of libdebpackages.

 -- Doug Barbieri <doug@m2osw.com>  Fri, 05 Apr 2013 11:38:44 -0800

pkg-explorer (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial version
  * Support for importing packages (install from file system), removing, and initialzing root db folder.

